<L>__{exterior black rock day (dawn)}
<A>__{liz's jeep, driven by macreedy, rolls slowly down the empty main street of the sleeping town. behind him, under a tarp, the body of the girl lies lifeless across the seat. on the seat beside him is smith's rifle, the balance a few inches from macreedy's elbow. on the right front fender of the jeep smith sits precariously, his shirt scorched and ragged. he wears a sullen expression of pained indifference. in b.g., as the jeep passes, isolated lights go on, first in doc's house, then in two or three others. macreedy is oblivious to them.}
